<title>Units</title>


<p>Pretext doesn't have great support for units, but they are very important for engineering, so I have cobbled together a workaround.  This isn't valid pretext, so it won't validate with the standard schema, but you can use weh-pretext.rncm in the custom folder to get it to validate.</p>
<p>It it will be expanded to valid pretext syntax before the output is made.  </p>
<p>weh</p>
<p>Whenever you have a quantity with units, you need to include it in the source code like this, and put this in a math environment like <tag>m</tag>, <tag>me</tag>, or <tag>md</tag>.</p>
<p><tag> qty units='N'</tag></p>
<p>The values inside the tag can be a bare number, or any valid math.</p>
<p>By doing this, when the book is turned into html or pdf, the units will be rendered correctly, Upright font in a math environment, superscripts etc.</p>
<p>See samples below.</p>
<p>These abbreviations get translated by my units.xsl which is called as part of scriv2ptx.xsl</p>
